oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Postcard, "Motor Cycle Gunners."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A postcard featuring a color-tinted photograph of two motorcycles with sidecars, two soldiers riding each. They are in a grassy field. The title at top is "Motor Cycle Gunners." At lower right corner is "Copy Press Ill Service Inc." Reverse is stamped with advertisement for Smiths Variety Store, Wayside, W. Va. Collected by Ethel Flesher Stewart of Parkersburg, W. Va.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
